http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/12-gamblers-apprehended/article13993632.ece

In a raid conducted as part of a stepped up vigil against gambling and cockfights, the Nellore town police apprehended 12 persons and seized Rs. 88,000 from them when they were indulging in gambling in a room in Hotel Haritha here on Sunday.Town DSP G.V. Ramudu along with his staff raided the hotel room following information that gamblers had been frequently meeting there. The raid was made in the room No. 402.Stating that Sankranti festival season holidays were being used for increasing gambling activities from hidden places, Mr. Ramudu warned that stringent action would be taken if anybody was found to be involved in gambling.